heading_context: Reclaim VAT on a self build home
chunks.html_content:
You can apply for a VAT refund on building materials and services if you’re:

  • building a new home (a ‘self build’)
  • converting a property into a home
  • building a non-profit communal residence, for example a hospice
  • building a property for a charity

This is known as the ‘DIY housebuilders’ scheme’. You can only make one claim for a VAT refund under the scheme.

heading_context: Reclaim VAT on a self build home
chunks.html_content:
If you completed building work before 5 December 2023, you must apply no more than 3 months after finishing.

If you completed building work on or after 5 December 2023, you must apply no more than 6 months after finishing.
